rComments: Physics is really hard, but professor Wong is the best teacher for it. His lectures are clear and he goes through many problems together so you can understand the really hard concepts. His midterms and exams are really flexible in terms of grading weight which makes them less intimidating. Would definitely take again.
He really cares about his students! love the guy ! he also responds to emails 30 seconds after you sent them and he's always pleasant to talk to. :)
He's honestly the best physics prof I've had.

Only had him as a lab coordinator but he is very considerate with students circumstances, especially given the global pandemic. I had an issue with submitting my lab report late and he just extended it for me. Lab quizzes and reports are pretty straight forward and don't take too long in comparison to other labs. Great coordinator and great person.

Great Lab coordinator for PHY1331. Very considerate and the labs are reasonable. Only take a few hours (4-5 max), to get them done. Not too hard questions. I love how straightforward it is, you do everything he says and get all the answers correct, you will get full marks. Criticism I would say maybe the quizes only being open in short window.
Best labs. Very considerate.

Very unhelpful as a professor. I'm sure he's a nice guy but his in-class examples were not as helpful as he claims in preparing for his exams. Exams were very difficult and all multiple choice or fill in the blank so no room for part marks even though he says he gives part marks somehow. He is a good lab coordinator and I wish he stayed as that.

To be honest with you, I think the only professor who gets it is Professor Wong. He understands that his students have a busy life and semester. He will definitely help you out whenever you need help. His lectures are very structured which is good and he cares. He cares about his students. Physics is usually a tough course but he makes it doable.

Nice guy, good prof. He gives extra test-like (optional) problems with full solutions after each lecture. Tests are reasonable. Very timely email replies. Lab instructions are clear. You do everything that's listed on the paper, full marks. Very straightforward. Labs take 3-6 hours depending on how you choose to do them (by hand, word, LaTeX,...)

Lab coordinator for first year physics course. Due to everything being online so were the labs, and professor Wong ignored my emails asking him to post the previous completed lab answers to avoid making the same mistakes. Still no answer and no correcting scheme, the labs are all done at this point. Not helpful.

His teaching style is reading off the slides and expecting you to memorize what he says. He mainly goes through theory and formula derivations, all of which are not covered on the exams. The lab component was fine and fairly easy. His marking schemes grant you an opportunity to go over 100%, but that only happens if you study hard, so be careful.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'EXTRA CREDIT', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Wong is a real gem because he gives so many extra marks. Both midterms had free bonus marks on it as well as the final. These can easily boost a B to an A- or an A- to an A+. Quiz questions are mostly easy As as long as you do the practice problems beforehand as they are pretty much identical. One of the best physics profs for sure.
As easy and accessible as physics can be. Keep up with the work and he will mark fairly

He gave the whole class free participation marks because enough people showed up for class every week. Also you have to work hard the whole semester cause there's a lot of different things you need to do to get marks like quizzes and labs and two midterms. Work on the quiz problems every week to keep up with the class or you'll get lost.

Really nice prof. First midterm was a breeze, second midterm was tough but he curved a lot, final was long but fair. Labs and quizzes are free. People that are complaining are naive, physics is hard and you shouldn't expect it to be handed to you on a silver platter. If you think Wong is a tough prof you're gonna have a bad time in second year.

He's an incredible prof and students don't give him credit for it. He's very funny and "cool with the kids" as they say. You just have to email him and he's always willing to help you learn the content. Labs are super easy and quizzes are basically handed to you as the questions are given a week in advance for you to prepare along with quiz dates.

I'll be honest the prof is a pretty chill dude and the course material isn't too difficult but in reality this isn't reflected when it comes to his midterms and exams. This guy has 0 chill when it comes to tests and you'll literally be sweating to answer everything because he makes it so damn long and hard. Would not recommend this at all.
very generous in giving extra marks.

do yourself a favour and take this class in summer with Dr. Wong unless you want to suffer to Badolato or stadnik. Exams were half multiple choice and half long answer and he curved the midterm and not sure about final. If yuo meet him during office hours then he will help you understand whatever you missed in class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Not my best performance. Anyway, he is that kind of Prof that wants everyone to succeed and he's chill. He creates chances for people to get easy points. Just study for quizzes, assignments, Dgd etc. It's not hard as u think. U will do fine

You have to study all the assigned problems in DGDs, quizzes, and assignments in order to do well on the midterm and final. He was available all the time for help. I liked the demos but sometimes they went on too long. Lots of ways to get bonus marks on quizzes and the midterm/final but sometimes they are random "What soccer team will win WC??"
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: The teacher is good as a person but when it came to teaching it was horrible. He did not know the concepts we were learning therefore could not answer are questions right. He did want feedback from the class and listened to it mostly. His tests are very long and very hard. I had to self teach myself everything from the manuals.

concepts were pretty easy to understand. but classes are a drag. if it werent for the quizzes we did in class, i probably would have skipped all the lectures. Tests are annoying and long. 5 steps for a single multiple choice and the equation sheets doesnt have all the equations. tests dont reflect what we do in class so studying kinda sucks

bad prof. tests dont reflect the course material and he just talks to himself with a boring and monotone voice. useless prof and doesnt even have a phd. its a shame that i had to wast my summer taking physics with this clown. better have a bellcurve since he pulls the questions out of his assss.
